{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KAvPmCVVWzXjeZSWud4oJp","type":"tool_result","content":"     1в†’# Specification: 008 User Profile вЂ” Transaction History\n     2в†’\n     3в†’## Meta\n     4в†’\n     5в†’| Field | Value |\n     6в†’|-------|-------|\n     7в†’| Status | Ready |\n     8в†’| Priority | P1 |\n     9в†’| Phase | 3 |\n    10в†’| NR_OF_TRIES | 8 |\n    11в†’\n    12в†’---\n    13в†’\n    14в†’## Overview\n    15в†’\n    16в†’First iteration of player profiles. Players can view a chronological list of\n    17в†’their own game transactions вЂ” joins, wins, losses, and refunds вЂ” across all\n    18в†’games (Coinflip, Lord of the RNGs, Close Call). Data is stored in a new\n    19в†’backend ledger table and served via an authenticated API endpoint. The\n    20в†’existing mock-driven `ProfileTransactions` frontend component is wired to the\n    21в†’real data.\n    22в†’\n    23в†’No on-chain footprint. No aggregate stats, XP, levels, or social features in\n    24в†’this iteration.\n    25в†’\n    26в†’## User Stories\n    27в†’\n    28в†’- As a player, I want to see every game transaction tied to my wallet so I can\n    29в†’  track what I wagered, won, or lost.\n    30в†’- As a player, I want the list to update automatically after a game settles so\n    31в†’  I don't have to refresh.\n    32в†’\n    33в†’---\n    34в†’\n    35в†’## Scope Alignment\n    36в†’\n    37в†’- **`docs/SCOPE.md` references**: Phase 3 вЂ” \"Basic player profile/history from\n    38в†’  indexed data\"; Launch checklist вЂ” \"Basic profile/history available and\n    39в†’  accurate\"\n    40в†’- **Scope status**: V1 In Scope\n    41в†’- **Phase boundary**: Phase 3\n    42в†’\n    43в†’## Required Context Files\n    44в†’\n    45в†’- `services/backend/src/db.ts` вЂ” DB client & query functions\n    46в†’- `services/backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts` вЂ” settlement write path (coinflip + lord)\n    47в†’- `services/backend/src/worker/closecall-clock.ts` вЂ” closecall settlement write path (settleRound function)\n    48в†’- `services/backend/src/routes/` вЂ” existing route patterns\n    49в†’- `services/backend/migrations/` вЂ” migration files (see Developer Reference below)\n    50в†’- `apps/platform/src/features/player-profile/` вЂ” mock profile system + components\n    51в†’\n    52в†’## Contract Files\n    53в†’\n    54в†’- `apps/platform/src/features/player-profile/types.ts` вЂ” `ProfileTransaction` type (frontend shape)\n    55в†’- `apps/platform/src/features/player-profile/components/ProfileTransactions.tsx` вЂ” table component to wire\n    56в†’\n    57в†’---\n    58в†’\n    59в†’## Functional Requirements\n    60в†’\n    61в†’### FR-1: `user_transactions` Ledger Table\n    62в†’\n    63в†’A new PostgreSQL table that stores one row per user-visible game event.\n    64в†’\n    65в†’**Schema:**\n    66в†’\n    67в†’| Column | Type | Constraints | Notes |\n    68в†’|--------|------|-------------|-------|\n    69в†’| `id` | `BIGSERIAL` | PK | Auto-increment |\n    70в†’| `wallet` | `TEXT` | NOT NULL | Player wallet address |\n    71в†’| `game` | `TEXT` | NOT NULL | `coinflip`, `lord`, `closecall` |\n    72в†’| `match_id` | `TEXT` | NOT NULL | Links to rounds/closecall_rounds |\n    73в†’| `event` | `TEXT` | NOT NULL | `join`, `win`, `loss`, `refund` |\n    74в†’| `amount_lamports` | `BIGINT` | NOT NULL | Wager (join) or payout (win) or refund amount |\n    75в†’| `tx_sig` | `TEXT` | | On-chain transaction signature (nullable until confirmed) |\n    76в†’| `created_at` | `TIMESTAMPTZ` | NOT NULL DEFAULT now() | Event timestamp |\n    77в†’\n    78в†’**Indexes:**\n    79в†’- `idx_user_tx_wallet_created` on `(wallet, created_at DESC)` вЂ” paginated history\n    80в†’- `idx_user_tx_match_id` on `(match_id)` вЂ” dedup / lookup\n    81в†’\n    82в†’**Acceptance Criteria:**\n    83в†’- [ ] Migration `007_user_transactions.sql` creates the table and indexes\n    84в†’- [ ] Migration runs cleanly on a fresh DB and on an existing DB\n    85в†’- [ ] No backfill of historical data (table starts empty)\n    86в†’\n    87в†’### FR-2: Write Path вЂ” Populate on Settlement\n    88в†’\n    89в†’The settlement worker writes to `user_transactions` when a round settles.\n    90в†’All writes use `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING` on `(wallet, match_id, event)` for\n    91в†’idempotency.\n    92в†’\n    93в†’**Coinflip** (commit-reveal, 1v1):\n    94в†’- **Join вЂ” creator**: Written when the create route inserts the round into DB\n    95в†’  (creator wallet is known at create time).\n    96в†’- **Join вЂ” opponent**: Written when PDA watcher detects phase change to LOCKED\n    97в†’  (opponent wallet readable from on-chain account).\n    98в†’- **Win + Loss**: On `settle_confirmed` in `settle-tx.ts`, insert two rows.\n    99в†’  `win.amount_lamports` = payout (after fees). `loss.amount_lamports` =\n   100в†’  original wager.\n   101в†’\n   102в†’**Lord of the RNGs** (commit-reveal, multi-player):\n   103в†’- **No join rows** вЂ” the PDA watcher sees the round state change but not\n   104в†’  individual entries. Join visibility is deferred.\n   105в†’- **Win + Loss**: On `settle_confirmed` in `settle-tx.ts`, insert one `win`\n   106в†’  row for the winner and one `loss` row per losing entry. Entries array is\n   107в†’  available from on-chain round data at settlement time.\n   108в†’\n   109в†’**Close Call** (pari-mutuel):\n   110в†’- **All rows at settlement**: When `settleRound()` in `closecall-clock.ts`\n   111в†’  completes, write one `join` + one outcome (`win`/`loss`/`refund`) row per\n   112в†’  entry. Entries are in the round's `green_entries`/`red_entries` JSONB.\n   113в†’- **Refund rows**: Only Close Call has backend-processed refunds (one-sided\n   114в†’  rounds, single player, equal price). Coinflip/Lord refunds are\n   115в†’  permissionless on-chain timeout вЂ” the backend doesn't process them.\n   116в†’\n   117в†’**Game name mapping**: DB stores `coinflip`, `lord`, `closecall`. API maps to\n   118в†’frontend `GameId`: `lord` в†’ `lord-of-rngs`, `closecall` в†’ `close-call`.\n   119в†’\n   120в†’**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   121в†’- [ ] Coinflip: creator join row written at create time\n   122в†’- [ ] Coinflip: opponent join row written at PDA watcher lock detection\n   123в†’- [ ] Coinflip: win + loss rows written at settlement with correct amounts and tx_sig\n   124в†’- [ ] Lord: win row for winner + loss rows for all losers at settlement\n   125в†’- [ ] Close Call: join + outcome rows per entry at settlement\n   126в†’- [ ] Close Call: refund rows written for refund outcomes\n   127в†’- [ ] `match_id` links back to the correct round in `rounds` or `closecall_rounds`\n   128в†’- [ ] No duplicate rows for the same event (idempotent via ON CONFLICT)\n   129в†’\n   130в†’### FR-3: API Endpoint вЂ” Transaction History\n   131в†’\n   132в†’```\n   133в†’GET /profile/transactions?cursor=<id>&limit=<n>&game=<filter>\n   134в†’```\n   135в†’\n   136в†’- **Auth**: JWT required. Returns transactions only for the authenticated\n   137в†’  wallet (from JWT `sub` claim). No wallet parameter in URL вЂ” prevents\n   138в†’  enumeration.\n   139в†’- **Pagination**: Cursor-based using `id` (descending). Default limit 20,\n   140в†’  max 50.\n   141в†’- **Filtering**: Optional `game` query param (`coinflip`, `lord`, `closecall`).\n   142в†’- **Response shape**:\n   143в†’  ```json\n   144в†’  {\n   145в†’    \"transactions\": [\n   146в†’      {\n   147в†’        \"id\": 123,\n   148в†’        \"game\": \"coinflip\",\n   149в†’        \"matchId\": \"a1b2c3d4e5f67890\",\n   150в†’        \"event\": \"win\",\n   151в†’        \"amountLamports\": \"5000000\",\n   152в†’        \"txSig\": \"5KtP...\",\n   153в†’        \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-19T12:00:00Z\"\n   154в†’      }\n   155в†’    ],\n   156в†’    \"nextCursor\": \"122\"\n   157в†’  }\n   158в†’  ```\n   159в†’- `amountLamports` serialized as string (BigInt safety).\n   160в†’\n   161в†’**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   162в†’- [ ] Endpoint requires valid JWT; returns 401 without one\n   163в†’- [ ] Returns only transactions for the authenticated wallet\n   164в†’- [ ] Cursor-based pagination works correctly (forward traversal)\n   165в†’- [ ] `game` filter restricts results to the specified game\n   166в†’- [ ] Default limit is 20; max clamped to 50\n   167в†’- [ ] Response matches the documented shape\n   168в†’- [ ] Empty result returns `{ \"transactions\": [], \"nextCursor\": null }`\n   169в†’\n   170в†’### FR-4: Frontend вЂ” Wire ProfileTransactions to Real Data\n   171в†’\n   172в†’Replace mock transaction data in the profile page with real API calls.\n   173в†’\n   174в†’- Fetch from `GET /profile/transactions` using the existing auth token.\n   175в†’- Infinite scroll or \"load more\" pagination using `nextCursor`.\n   176в†’- Show loading skeleton while fetching.\n   177в†’- Show empty state when no transactions exist.\n   178в†’- Each row links to the match deep-link page (`/coinflip/:matchId`,\n   179в†’  `/lord-of-rngs/:matchId`, `/close-call/:matchId`).\n   180в†’\n   181в†’**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   182в†’- [ ] Profile transactions tab fetches from the real endpoint\n   183в†’- [ ] Pagination loads more results on scroll/click\n   184в†’- [ ] Loading and empty states render correctly\n   185в†’- [ ] Transaction rows link to the correct game match page\n   186в†’- [ ] Amounts display in SOL with USD estimate (via Pyth SOL/USD feed)\n   187в†’- [ ] Mock transaction generation is removed or bypassed when real data is available\n   188в†’\n   189в†’### FR-5: SOL/USD Price Display\n   190в†’\n   191в†’Transaction amounts are stored in lamports. The frontend displays them in SOL\n   192в†’with a USD estimate using the Pyth SOL/USD price feed (Hermes REST API вЂ”\n   193в†’already used for Close Call BTC/USD prices).\n   194в†’\n   195в†’- Backend exposes a cached `GET /price/sol-usd` endpoint (or piggybacks on an\n   196в†’  existing price infrastructure). Cache TTL ~60s.\n   197в†’- Frontend fetches the SOL/USD price and displays amounts as e.g.\n   198в†’  `0.50 SOL (~$75.00)`.\n   199в†’- If price is unavailable, show SOL amount only (no USD estimate). No error\n   200в†’  state вЂ” graceful degradation.\n   201в†’\n   202в†’**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   203в†’- [ ] Backend serves cached SOL/USD price from Pyth Hermes\n   204в†’- [ ] Frontend displays lamport amounts as SOL with USD estimate\n   205в†’- [ ] Graceful fallback to SOL-only when price unavailable\n   206в†’\n   207в†’---\n   208в†’\n   209в†’## Success Criteria\n   210в†’\n   211в†’- A player who completes a game sees the transaction appear in their profile\n   212в†’  within seconds of settlement\n   213в†’- Transaction list is accurate вЂ” amounts, outcomes, and game types match\n   214в†’  on-chain reality\n   215в†’- Profile page loads transaction history performantly (< 500ms for first page)\n   216в†’\n   217в†’---\n   218в†’\n   219в†’## Dependencies\n   220в†’\n   221в†’- JWT auth system (spec 007 вЂ” already shipped)\n   222в†’- Settlement worker (coinflip + lord + closecall вЂ” already shipped)\n   223в†’- PDA watcher for join detection (already shipped)\n   224в†’\n   225в†’## Assumptions\n   226в†’\n   227в†’- No backfill of historical data вЂ” table starts empty, only new events recorded\n   228в†’- Close Call enforces one entry per player per round (on-chain constraint)\n   229в†’- No aggregate stats (win rate, total wagered, P&L) in this iteration\n   230в†’- No other players' transaction visibility вЂ” own wallet only\n   231в†’\n   232в†’---\n   233в†’\n   234в†’## Developer Reference\n   235в†’\n   236в†’> These notes exist so the implementor doesn't have to re-discover project\n   237в†’> conventions each time.\n   238в†’\n   239в†’### Database & Migrations\n   240в†’\n   241в†’| What | Where |\n   242в†’|------|-------|\n   243в†’| Migration files | `services/backend/migrations/NNN_snake_name.sql` |\n   244в†’| Migration runner | `services/backend/src/migrate.ts` вЂ” auto-runs on server start (`pnpm start` = `migrate && server`) |\n   245в†’| DB client + query fns | `services/backend/src/db.ts` |\n   246в†’| DB config (schema) | `services/backend/src/db-config.ts` вЂ” supports `DB_SCHEMA` env var |\n   247в†’| Connection library | `postgres` (v3.4.0) вЂ” tagged template literal style |\n   248в†’\n   249в†’**Naming**: Files are `NNN_description.sql` where NNN is zero-padded sequential.\n   250в†’Next available: `007`.\n   251в†’\n   252в†’**Runner behavior**: Reads `migrations/` dir, parses version from filename\n   253в†’prefix, tracks applied versions in `_migrations` table, applies pending ones\n   254в†’inside `sql.begin()` transactions. Idempotent вЂ” safe to re-run.\n   255в†’\n   256в†’**Manual run**: `cd services/backend && pnpm migrate` (uses `.env`).\n   257в†’**Check status**: `pnpm migrate:status`.\n   258в†’\n   259в†’### Settlement Write Paths (where to add INSERTs)\n   260в†’\n   261в†’| Game | File | Function | Insert after |\n   262в†’|------|------|----------|-------------|\n   263в†’| Coinflip settle | `src/worker/settle-tx.ts` | `settleMatch()` | After `settle_confirmed` operator event (~line 286) |\n   264в†’| Lord settle | `src/worker/settle-tx.ts` | `settleLordRound()` | After `settle_confirmed` operator event (~line 466) |\n   265в†’| Close Call settle | `src/worker/closecall-clock.ts` | `settleRound()` | After DB update (~line 443-487) |\n   266в†’| Coinflip creator join | `src/routes/create.ts` | POST `/fairness/coinflip/create` | After round INSERT |\n   267в†’| Coinflip opponent join | `src/worker/pda-watcher.ts` | `handleCoinflipChange()` | After lock detection (~line 113) |\n   268в†’| Close Call join+outcome | `src/worker/closecall-clock.ts` | `settleRound()` | Same as settle вЂ” all rows at settlement |\n   269в†’\n   270в†’### Existing Schema (for reference)\n   271в†’\n   272в†’| Table | PK | Purpose |\n   273в†’|-------|----|---------|\n   274в†’| `rounds` | `pda` | Commit-reveal rounds (coinflip + lord). Has `creator`, `winner`, `settle_tx`, `amount_lamports`, `match_id` |\n   275в†’| `closecall_rounds` | `round_id` | Pari-mutuel rounds. Entries in JSONB: `green_entries` / `red_entries` = `[{ player, amountLamports }]` |\n   276в†’| `operator_events` | `id` | Audit log. `event_type` + JSONB `payload` |\n   277в†’| `auth_challenges` | `nonce` | JWT challenge nonces |\n   278в†’| `refresh_tokens` | `id` | JWT refresh token families |\n   279в†’| `closecall_candles` | `minute_ts` | Cached Hermes BTC prices |\n   280в†’\n   281в†’---\n   282в†’\n   283в†’## Validation Plan\n   284в†’\n   285в†’| # | Acceptance Criterion | Validation Method | Evidence Required |\n   286в†’|---|---------------------|-------------------|-------------------|\n   287в†’| 1 | Migration creates table + indexes | Run `pnpm migrate` on fresh + existing DB | Migration status shows applied |\n   288в†’| 2 | Settlement writes correct rows | Settle a coinflip match on devnet, query table | Row with correct wallet, game, event, amount, tx_sig |\n   289в†’| 3 | API returns own transactions only | Call endpoint with two different JWTs | Each sees only their own rows |\n   290в†’| 4 | Pagination works | Insert > 20 rows, paginate | Second page returns remaining rows |\n   291в†’| 5 | Frontend displays real data | Play a game, check profile page | Transaction appears with correct details |\n   292в†’\n   293в†’---\n   294в†’\n   295в†’## Completion Signal\n   296в†’\n   297в†’### Implementation Checklist\n   298в†’\n   299в†’- [x] [engine] Migration `007_user_transactions.sql` вЂ” create table with schema from FR-1 (id, wallet, game, match_id, event, amount_lamports, tx_sig, created_at) + indexes `idx_user_tx_wallet_created` and `idx_user_tx_match_id` + UNIQUE constraint on `(wallet, match_id, event)` for idempotency. Add `insertUserTransaction()` and `getUserTransactions(wallet, cursor?, limit?, game?)` query functions to `db.ts`. Verify migration runs cleanly: `cd services/backend && pnpm migrate:status`. (done: iteration 1)\n   300в†’- [x] [engine] Coinflip write paths вЂ” (a) In `src/routes/create.ts`: after inserting round into DB, write a `join` row for the creator (wallet = creator, game = \"coinflip\", amount_lamports = wager). (b) In `src/worker/pda-watcher.ts` `handleCoinflipChange()`: after lock detection (~line 113), read opponent from on-chain account, write a `join` row for the opponent. (c) In `src/worker/settle-tx.ts` `settleMatch()`: after `settle_confirmed` event (~line 286), write one `win` row (amount_lamports = payoutAmount) and one `loss` row (amount_lamports = original wager) with tx_sig. All writes use `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING`. (done: iteration 2)\n   301в†’- [x] [engine] Lord of the RNGs write paths вЂ” In `src/worker/settle-tx.ts` `settleLordRound()`: after `settle_confirmed` event (~line 466), write one `win` row for the winner (amount_lamports = payoutAmount) and one `loss` row per losing entry (amount_lamports = that entry's amountLamports). Entries array is available from `roundData.entries`. Game = \"lord\". No join rows for Lord (deferred вЂ” PDA watcher doesn't see individual entries). All writes use `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING`. (done: iteration 3)\n   302в†’- [x] [engine] Close Call write paths вЂ” In `src/worker/closecall-clock.ts` `settleRound()`: after DB settle update (~line 487), iterate `green_entries` and `red_entries` arrays. For each entry write: (a) one `join` row (amount_lamports = entry.amountLamports), (b) one outcome row вЂ” `win` (amount_lamports = computed payout) if entry is on winning side, `loss` (amount_lamports = entry.amountLamports) if losing side, or `refund` (amount_lamports = entry.amountLamports) if `isRefund`. Game = \"closecall\", match_id = round_id. Payout per winner = `(entryAmount / winningSidePool) * (totalPool - fee)`. All writes use `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING`. (done: iteration 4)\n   303в†’- [x] [engine] API route `GET /profile/transactions` вЂ” Add `src/routes/profile.ts`, register at `/profile/transactions`. Require JWT auth middleware (reuse existing). Extract wallet from `req.auth.sub`. Query params: `cursor` (id, optional), `limit` (default 20, max 50), `game` (optional filter вЂ” accept both DB names and frontend names: `lord`/`lord-of-rngs`, `closecall`/`close-call`). Call `db.getUserTransactions()`. Map response: `game` field mapped to frontend names (`lord` в†’ `lord-of-rngs`, `closecall` в†’ `close-call`), `amountLamports` as string, `matchId` camelCase. Return `{ transactions: [...], nextCursor: string | null }`. (done: iteration 5)\n   304в†’- [x] [engine] SOL/USD price endpoint вЂ” Add `GET /price/sol-usd` to backend. Fetch from Pyth Hermes REST API (SOL/USD feed ID: `0xef0d8b6fda2ceba41da15d4095d1da392a0d2f8ed0c6c7bc0f4cfac8c280b56d`). Cache in-memory with ~60s TTL. Response: `{ price: number, expo: number, updatedAt: string }`. No auth required (public endpoint). Reuse existing Hermes fetch patterns from `closecall-clock.ts`. (done: iteration 6)\n   305в†’- [x] [frontend] Wire `ProfileTransactions` to real API вЂ” Update `ProfileTransaction` type in `types.ts` to match API shape: add `event` field (`join`/`win`/`loss`/`refund`), rename `outcome` в†’ `event`, keep `gameId` mapped from API `game`. Create `useTransactions(cursor?, game?)` hook that calls `GET /profile/transactions` with auth header. Replace `getTransactions()` mock import in `ProfileTransactions.tsx` with the hook. Implement \"Load more\" button using `nextCursor`. Add loading skeleton and empty state. Each row links to deep-link page: `/coinflip/:matchId`, `/lord-of-rngs/:matchId`, `/close-call/:matchId` based on game. Display `join`/`win`/`loss`/`refund` event types with appropriate styling. (done: iteration 7)\n   306в†’- [x] [frontend] SOL amount display with USD estimate вЂ” Fetch SOL/USD price from `GET /price/sol-usd` (create `useSolPrice()` hook, cache in React state, refresh every 60s). Convert lamports в†’ SOL (`amount / 1e9`). Display as `\"0.50 SOL (~$75.00)\"`. If price unavailable, show SOL only (no error). Apply to all amount cells in `ProfileTransactions`. (done: iteration 8)\n   307в†’- [ ] [test] Add local deterministic E2E coverage for primary user flow(s) in `e2e/local/**` (or mark N/A with reason for non-web/non-interactive specs)\n   308в†’- [ ] [test] Add visual route/state coverage in `e2e/visual/**`; run `pnpm test:visual` and update baselines only for intentional UI changes\n   309в†’- [ ] [test] Update visual baselines for profile transactions page. Run `pnpm test:visual` to identify failures, then `pnpm test:visual:update` to regenerate. **Before committing**: read old baseline and new screenshot for each changed page (use Read tool on PNG files). Evaluate: **PASS** (changes clearly match spec intent, only expected areas changed) в†’ commit updated baselines. **REVIEW** (changes look plausible but unexpected areas also changed, or uncertain) в†’ do NOT commit baselines. Save the diff images from `test-results/` to `docs/specs/008-user-profile/visual-review/`, describe concerns in `history.md`, output `<blocker>Visual review needed: [describe what looks off]</blocker>`. **FAIL** (layout broken, elements missing, clearly wrong) в†’ fix the code, do NOT update baselines.\n   310в†’- [ ] [test] N/A вЂ” no external provider/oracle/VRF integration in scope for this spec\n   311в†’\n   312в†’### Testing Requirements\n   313в†’\n   314в†’The agent MUST complete ALL before outputting the completion signal:\n   315в†’\n   316в†’#### Code Quality\n   317в†’- [ ] All existing tests pass\n   318в†’- [ ] New tests added for new functionality\n   319в†’- [ ] No lint errors\n   320в†’\n   321в†’#### Functional Verification\n   322в†’- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified\n   323в†’- [ ] Edge cases handled\n   324в†’- [ ] Error states handled\n   325в†’\n   326в†’#### Visual Regression\n   327в†’- [ ] `pnpm test:visual` passes (all baselines match)\n   328в†’- [ ] If this spec changes UI: affected baselines regenerated and committed\n   329в†’- [ ] Local deterministic E2E passes (`pnpm test:e2e`) for user-facing flows\n   330в†’- [ ] Devnet real-provider E2E: N/A for this spec\n   331в†’\n   332в†’#### Visual Verification (if UI)\n   333в†’- [ ] Desktop view correct\n   334в†’- [ ] Mobile view correct\n   335в†’\n   336в†’#### Console/Network Check (if web)\n   337в†’- [ ] No JS console errors\n   338в†’- [ ] No failed network requests\n   339в†’\n   340в†’#### Smoke Test (Human-in-the-Loop)\n   341в†’\n   342в†’- [ ] Settle a coinflip match в†’ transaction appears in profile within seconds\n   343в†’- [ ] Settle a lord round в†’ transaction appears in profile\n   344в†’- [ ] Place a closecall bet + settle в†’ join and result rows appear\n   345в†’- [ ] Pagination loads older transactions correctly\n   346в†’- [ ] Amounts shown in SOL with USD estimate, match on-chain values\n   347в†’- [ ] Empty profile shows clean empty state, not broken UI\n   348в†’- [ ] Unauthenticated request returns 401, not data\n   349в†’\n   350в†’### Iteration Instructions\n   351в†’\n   352в†’If ANY check fails:\n   353в†’1. Identify the specific issue\n   354в†’2. Fix the code\n   355в†’3. Re-run tests\n   356в†’4. Re-verify all criteria\n   357в†’5. Check again\n   358в†’\n   359в†’**Only when ALL checks pass, output:** `<promise>DONE</promise>`\n   360в†’\n   361в†’### Post-Completion: Gap Analysis\n   362в†’\n   363в†’After the spec loop outputs `<promise>DONE</promise>`, `spec-loop.sh` automatically runs\n   364в†’`/gap-analysis {id} --non-interactive` which:\n   365в†’1. Audits every FR acceptance criterion against the codebase\n   366в†’2. Writes `docs/specs/008-user-profile/gap-analysis.md` with inventory + audit + recommendations\n   367в†’3. Annotates FR checkboxes with HTML comment evidence (`<!-- satisfied: ... -->`)\n   368в†’4. Commits everything together with the completion commit\n   369в†’"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b99e2185-20b1-487e-a0a4-b3fb9a756d45","uuid":"2e1375bf-177f-4d58-b302-a489052cbfcd","timestamp":"2026-03-19T19:12:07.019Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/008-user-profile/spec.md","content":"# Specification: 008 User Profile вЂ” Transaction History\n\n## Meta\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| Status | Ready |\n| Priority | P1 |\n| Phase | 3 |\n| NR_OF_TRIES | 8 |\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nFirst iteration of player profiles. Players can view a chronological list of\ntheir own game transactions вЂ” joins, wins, losses, and refunds вЂ” across all\ngames (Coinflip, Lord of the RNGs, Close Call). Data is stored in a new\nbackend ledger table and served via an authenticated API endpoint. The\nexisting mock-driven `ProfileTransactions` frontend component is wired to the\nreal data.\n\nNo on-chain footprint. No aggregate stats, XP, levels, or social features in\nthis iteration.\n\n## User Stories\n\n- As a player, I want to see every game transaction tied to my wallet so I can\n  track what I wagered, won, or lost.\n- As a player, I want the list to update automatically after a game settles so\n  I don't have to refresh.\n\n---\n\n## Scope Alignment\n\n- **`docs/SCOPE.md` references**: Phase 3 вЂ” \"Basic player profile/history from\n  indexed data\"; Launch checklist вЂ” \"Basic profile/history available and\n  accurate\"\n- **Scope status**: V1 In Scope\n- **Phase boundary**: Phase 3\n\n## Required Context Files\n\n- `services/backend/src/db.ts` вЂ” DB client & query functions\n- `services/backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts` вЂ” settlement write path (coinflip + lord)\n- `services/backend/src/worker/closecall-clock.ts` вЂ” closecall settlement write path (settleRound function)\n- `services/backend/src/routes/` вЂ” existing route patterns\n- `services/backend/migrations/` вЂ” migration files (see Developer Reference below)\n- `apps/platform/src/features/player-profile/` вЂ” mock profile system + components\n\n## Contract Files\n\n- `apps/platform/src/features/player-profile/types.ts` вЂ” `ProfileTransaction` type (frontend shape)\n- `apps/platform/src/features/player-profile/components/ProfileTransactions.tsx` вЂ” table component to wire\n\n---\n\n## Functional Requirements\n\n### FR-1: `user_transactions` Ledger Table\n\nA new PostgreSQL table that stores one row per user-visible game event.\n\n**Schema:**\n\n| Column | Type | Constraints | Notes |\n|--------|------|-------------|-------|\n| `id` | `BIGSERIAL` | PK | Auto-increment |\n| `wallet` | `TEXT` | NOT NULL | Player wallet address |\n| `game` | `TEXT` | NOT NULL | `coinflip`, `lord`, `closecall` |\n| `match_id` | `TEXT` | NOT NULL | Links to rounds/closecall_rounds |\n| `event` | `TEXT` | NOT NULL | `join`, `win`, `loss`, `refund` |\n| `amount_lamports` | `BIGINT` | NOT NULL | Wager (join) or payout (win) or refund amount |\n| `tx_sig` | `TEXT` | | On-chain transaction signature (nullable until confirmed) |\n| `created_at` | `TIMESTAMPTZ` | NOT NULL DEFAULT now() | Event timestamp |\n\n**Indexes:**\n- `idx_user_tx_wallet_created` on `(wallet, created_at DESC)` вЂ” paginated history\n- `idx_user_tx_match_id` on `(match_id)` вЂ” dedup / lookup\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Migration `007_user_transactions.sql` creates the table and indexes\n- [ ] Migration runs cleanly on a fresh DB and on an existing DB\n- [ ] No backfill of historical data (table starts empty)\n\n### FR-2: Write Path вЂ” Populate on Settlement\n\nThe settlement worker writes to `user_transactions` when a round settles.\nAll writes use `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING` on `(wallet, match_id, event)` for\nidempotency.\n\n**Coinflip** (commit-reveal, 1v1):\n- **Join вЂ” creator**: Written when the create route inserts the round into DB\n  (creator wallet is known at create time).\n- **Join вЂ” opponent**: Written when PDA watcher detects phase change to LOCKED\n  (opponent wallet readable from on-chain account).\n- **Win + Loss**: On `settle_confirmed` in `settle-tx.ts`, insert two rows.\n  `win.amount_lamports` = payout (after fees). `loss.amount_lamports` =\n  original wager.\n\n**Lord of the RNGs** (commit-reveal, multi-player):\n- **No join rows** вЂ” the PDA watcher sees the round state change but not\n  individual entries. Join visibility is deferred.\n- **Win + Loss**: On `settle_confirmed` in `settle-tx.ts`, insert one `win`\n  row for the winner and one `loss` row per losing entry. Entries array is\n  available from on-chain round data at settlement time.\n\n**Close Call** (pari-mutuel):\n- **All rows at settlement**: When `settleRound()` in `closecall-clock.ts`\n  completes, write one `join` + one outcome (`win`/`loss`/`refund`) row per\n  entry. Entries are in the round's `green_entries`/`red_entries` JSONB.\n- **Refund rows**: Only Close Call has backend-processed refunds (one-sided\n  rounds, single player, equal price). Coinflip/Lord refunds are\n  permissionless on-chain timeout вЂ” the backend doesn't process them.\n\n**Game name mapping**: DB stores `coinflip`, `lord`, `closecall`. API maps to\nfrontend `GameId`: `lord` в†’ `lord-of-rngs`, `closecall` в†’ `close-call`.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Coinflip: creator join row written at create time\n- [ ] Coinflip: opponent join row written at PDA watcher lock detection\n- [ ] Coinflip: win + loss rows written at settlement with correct amounts and tx_sig\n- [ ] Lord: win row for winner + loss rows for all losers at settlement\n- [ ] Close Call: join + outcome rows per entry at settlement\n- [ ] Close Call: refund rows written for refund outcomes\n- [ ] `match_id` links back to the correct round in `rounds` or `closecall_rounds`\n- [ ] No duplicate rows for the same event (idempotent via ON CONFLICT)\n\n### FR-3: API Endpoint вЂ” Transaction History\n\n```\nGET /profile/transactions?cursor=<id>&limit=<n>&game=<filter>\n```\n\n- **Auth**: JWT required. Returns transactions only for the authenticated\n  wallet (from JWT `sub` claim). No wallet parameter in URL вЂ” prevents\n  enumeration.\n- **Pagination**: Cursor-based using `id` (descending). Default limit 20,\n  max 50.\n- **Filtering**: Optional `game` query param (`coinflip`, `lord`, `closecall`).\n- **Response shape**:\n  ```json\n  {\n    \"transactions\": [\n      {\n        \"id\": 123,\n        \"game\": \"coinflip\",\n        \"matchId\": \"a1b2c3d4e5f67890\",\n        \"event\": \"win\",\n        \"amountLamports\": \"5000000\",\n        \"txSig\": \"5KtP...\",\n        \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-19T12:00:00Z\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"nextCursor\": \"122\"\n  }\n  ```\n- `amountLamports` serialized as string (BigInt safety).\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Endpoint requires valid JWT; returns 401 without one\n- [ ] Returns only transactions for the authenticated wallet\n- [ ] Cursor-based pagination works correctly (forward traversal)\n- [ ] `game` filter restricts results to the specified game\n- [ ] Default limit is 20; max clamped to 50\n- [ ] Response matches the documented shape\n- [ ] Empty result returns `{ \"transactions\": [], \"nextCursor\": null }`\n\n### FR-4: Frontend вЂ” Wire ProfileTransactions to Real Data\n\nReplace mock transaction data in the profile page with real API calls.\n\n- Fetch from `GET /profile/transactions` using the existing auth token.\n- Infinite scroll or \"load more\" pagination using `nextCursor`.\n- Show loading skeleton while fetching.\n- Show empty state when no transactions exist.\n- Each row links to the match deep-link page (`/coinflip/:matchId`,\n  `/lord-of-rngs/:matchId`, `/close-call/:matchId`).\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Profile transactions tab fetches from the real endpoint\n- [ ] Pagination loads more results on scroll/click\n- [ ] Loading and empty states render correctly\n- [ ] Transaction rows link to the correct game match page\n- [ ] Amounts display in SOL with USD estimate (via Pyth SOL/USD feed)\n- [ ] Mock transaction generation is removed or bypassed when real data is available\n\n### FR-5: SOL/USD Price Display\n\nTransaction amounts are stored in lamports. The frontend displays them in SOL\nwith a USD estimate using the Pyth SOL/USD price feed (Hermes REST API вЂ”\nalready used for Close Call BTC/USD prices).\n\n- Backend exposes a cached `GET /price/sol-usd` endpoint (or piggybacks on an\n  existing price infrastructure). Cache TTL ~60s.\n- Frontend fetches the SOL/USD price and displays amounts as e.g.\n  `0.50 SOL (~$75.00)`.\n- If price is unavailable, show SOL amount only (no USD estimate). No error\n  state вЂ” graceful degradation.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Backend serves cached SOL/USD price from Pyth Hermes\n- [ ] Frontend displays lamport amounts as SOL with USD estimate\n- [ ] Graceful fallback to SOL-only when price unavailable\n\n---\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- A player who completes a game sees the transaction appear in their profile\n  within seconds of settlement\n- Transaction list is accurate вЂ” amounts, outcomes, and game types match\n  on-chain reality\n- Profile page loads transaction history performantly (< 500ms for first page)\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- JWT auth system (spec 007 вЂ” already shipped)\n- Settlement worker (coinflip + lord + closecall вЂ” already shipped)\n- PDA watcher for join detection (already shipped)\n\n## Assumptions\n\n- No backfill of historical data вЂ” table starts empty, only new events recorded\n- Close Call enforces one entry per player per round (on-chain constraint)\n- No aggregate stats (win rate, total wagered, P&L) in this iteration\n- No other players' transaction visibility вЂ” own wallet only\n\n---\n\n## Developer Reference\n\n> These notes exist so the implementor doesn't have to re-discover project\n> conventions each time.\n\n### Database & Migrations\n\n| What | Where |\n|------|-------|\n| Migration files | `services/backend/migrations/NNN_snake_name.sql` |\n| Migration runner | `services/backend/src/migrate.ts` вЂ” auto-runs on server start (`pnpm start` = `migrate && server`) |\n| DB client + query fns | `services/backend/src/db.ts` |\n| DB config (schema) | `services/backend/src/db-config.ts` вЂ” supports `DB_SCHEMA` env var |\n| Connection library | `postgres` (v3.4.0) вЂ” tagged template literal style |\n\n**Naming**: Files are `NNN_description.sql` where NNN is zero-padded sequential.\nNext available: `007`.\n\n**Runner behavior**: Reads `migrations/` dir, parses version from filename\nprefix, tracks applied versions in `_migrations` table, applies pending ones\ninside `sql.begin()` transactions. Idempotent вЂ” safe to re-run.\n\n**Manual run**: `cd services/backend && pnpm migrate` (uses `.env`).\n**Check status**: `pnpm migrate:status`.\n\n### Settlement Write Paths (where to add INSERTs)\n\n| Game | File | Function | Insert after |\n|------|------|----------|-------------|\n| Coinflip settle | `src/worker/settle-tx.ts` | `settleMatch()` | After `settle_confirmed` operator event (~line 286) |\n| Lord settle | `src/worker/settle-tx.ts` | `settleLordRound()` | After `settle_confirmed` operator event (~line 466) |\n| Close Call settle | `src/worker/closecall-clock.ts` | `settleRound()` | After DB update (~line 443-487) |\n| Coinflip creator join | `src/routes/create.ts` | POST `/fairness/coinflip/create` | After round INSERT |\n| Coinflip opponent join | `src/worker/pda-watcher.ts` | `handleCoinflipChange()` | After lock detection (~line 113) |\n| Close Call join+outcome | `src/worker/closecall-clock.ts` | `settleRound()` | Same as settle вЂ” all rows at settlement |\n\n### Existing Schema (for reference)\n\n| Table | PK | Purpose |\n|-------|----|---------|\n| `rounds` | `pda` | Commit-reveal rounds (coinflip + lord). Has `creator`, `winner`, `settle_tx`, `amount_lamports`, `match_id` |\n| `closecall_rounds` | `round_id` | Pari-mutuel rounds. Entries in JSONB: `green_entries` / `red_entries` = `[{ player, amountLamports }]` |\n| `operator_events` | `id` | Audit log. `event_type` + JSONB `payload` |\n| `auth_challenges` | `nonce` | JWT challenge nonces |\n| `refresh_tokens` | `id` | JWT refresh token families |\n| `closecall_candles` | `minute_ts` | Cached Hermes BTC prices |\n\n---\n\n## Validation Plan\n\n| # | Acceptance Criterion | Validation Method | Evidence Required |\n|---|---------------------|-------------------|-------------------|\n| 1 | Migration creates table + indexes | Run `pnpm migrate` on fresh + existing DB | Migration status shows applied |\n| 2 | Settlement writes correct rows | Settle a coinflip match on devnet, query table | Row with correct wallet, game, event, amount, tx_sig |\n| 3 | API returns own transactions only | Call endpoint with two different JWTs | Each sees only their own rows |\n| 4 | Pagination works | Insert > 20 rows, paginate | Second page returns remaining rows |\n| 5 | Frontend displays real data | Play a game, check profile page | Transaction appears with correct details |\n\n---\n\n## Completion Signal\n\n### Implementation Checklist\n\n- [x] [engine] Migration `007_user_transactions.sql` вЂ” create table with schema from FR-1 (id, wallet, game, match_id, event, amount_lamports, tx_sig, created_at) + indexes `idx_user_tx_wallet_created` and `idx_user_tx_match_id` + UNIQUE constraint on `(wallet, match_id, event)` for idempotency. Add `insertUserTransaction()` and `getUserTransactions(wallet, cursor?, limit?, game?)` query functions to `db.ts`. Verify migration runs cleanly: `cd services/backend && pnpm migrate:status`. (done: iteration 1)\n- [x] [engine] Coinflip write paths вЂ” (a) In `src/routes/create.ts`: after inserting round into DB, write a `join` row for the creator (wallet = creator, game = \"coinflip\", amount_lamports = wager). (b) In `src/worker/pda-watcher.ts` `handleCoinflipChange()`: after lock detection (~line 113), read opponent from on-chain account, write a `join` row for the opponent. (c) In `src/worker/settle-tx.ts` `settleMatch()`: after `settle_confirmed` event (~line 286), write one `win` row (amount_lamports = payoutAmount) and one `loss` row (amount_lamports = original wager) with tx_sig. All writes use `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING`. (done: iteration 2)\n- [x] [engine] Lord of the RNGs write paths вЂ” In `src/worker/settle-tx.ts` `settleLordRound()`: after `settle_confirmed` event (~line 466), write one `win` row for the winner (amount_lamports = payoutAmount) and one `loss` row per losing entry (amount_lamports = that entry's amountLamports). Entries array is available from `roundData.entries`. Game = \"lord\". No join rows for Lord (deferred вЂ” PDA watcher doesn't see individual entries). All writes use `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING`. (done: iteration 3)\n- [x] [engine] Close Call write paths вЂ” In `src/worker/closecall-clock.ts` `settleRound()`: after DB settle update (~line 487), iterate `green_entries` and `red_entries` arrays. For each entry write: (a) one `join` row (amount_lamports = entry.amountLamports), (b) one outcome row вЂ” `win` (amount_lamports = computed payout) if entry is on winning side, `loss` (amount_lamports = entry.amountLamports) if losing side, or `refund` (amount_lamports = entry.amountLamports) if `isRefund`. Game = \"closecall\", match_id = round_id. Payout per winner = `(entryAmount / winningSidePool) * (totalPool - fee)`. All writes use `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING`. (done: iteration 4)\n- [x] [engine] API route `GET /profile/transactions` вЂ” Add `src/routes/profile.ts`, register at `/profile/transactions`. Require JWT auth middleware (reuse existing). Extract wallet from `req.auth.sub`. Query params: `cursor` (id, optional), `limit` (default 20, max 50), `game` (optional filter вЂ” accept both DB names and frontend names: `lord`/`lord-of-rngs`, `closecall`/`close-call`). Call `db.getUserTransactions()`. Map response: `game` field mapped to frontend names (`lord` в†’ `lord-of-rngs`, `closecall` в†’ `close-call`), `amountLamports` as string, `matchId` camelCase. Return `{ transactions: [...], nextCursor: string | null }`. (done: iteration 5)\n- [x] [engine] SOL/USD price endpoint вЂ” Add `GET /price/sol-usd` to backend. Fetch from Pyth Hermes REST API (SOL/USD feed ID: `0xef0d8b6fda2ceba41da15d4095d1da392a0d2f8ed0c6c7bc0f4cfac8c280b56d`). Cache in-memory with ~60s TTL. Response: `{ price: number, expo: number, updatedAt: string }`. No auth required (public endpoint). Reuse existing Hermes fetch patterns from `closecall-clock.ts`. (done: iteration 6)\n- [x] [frontend] Wire `ProfileTransactions` to real API вЂ” Update `ProfileTransaction` type in `types.ts` to match API shape: add `event` field (`join`/`win`/`loss`/`refund`), rename `outcome` в†’ `event`, keep `gameId` mapped from API `game`. Create `useTransactions(cursor?, game?)` hook that calls `GET /profile/transactions` with auth header. Replace `getTransactions()` mock import in `ProfileTransactions.tsx` with the hook. Implement \"Load more\" button using `nextCursor`. Add loading skeleton and empty state. Each row links to deep-link page: `/coinflip/:matchId`, `/lord-of-rngs/:matchId`, `/close-call/:matchId` based on game. Display `join`/`win`/`loss`/`refund` event types with appropriate styling. (done: iteration 7)\n- [x] [frontend] SOL amount display with USD estimate вЂ” Fetch SOL/USD price from `GET /price/sol-usd` (create `useSolPrice()` hook, cache in React state, refresh every 60s). Convert lamports в†’ SOL (`amount / 1e9`). Display as `\"0.50 SOL (~$75.00)\"`. If price unavailable, show SOL only (no error). Apply to all amount cells in `ProfileTransactions`. (done: iteration 8)\n- [ ] [test] Add local deterministic E2E coverage for primary user flow(s) in `e2e/local/**` (or mark N/A with reason for non-web/non-interactive specs)\n- [ ] [test] Add visual route/state coverage in `e2e/visual/**`; run `pnpm test:visual` and update baselines only for intentional UI changes\n- [ ] [test] Update visual baselines for profile transactions page. Run `pnpm test:visual` to identify failures, then `pnpm test:visual:update` to regenerate. **Before committing**: read old baseline and new screenshot for each changed page (use Read tool on PNG files). Evaluate: **PASS** (changes clearly match spec intent, only expected areas changed) в†’ commit updated baselines. **REVIEW** (changes look plausible but unexpected areas also changed, or uncertain) в†’ do NOT commit baselines. Save the diff images from `test-results/` to `docs/specs/008-user-profile/visual-review/`, describe concerns in `history.md`, output `<blocker>Visual review needed: [describe what looks off]</blocker>`. **FAIL** (layout broken, elements missing, clearly wrong) в†’ fix the code, do NOT update baselines.\n- [ ] [test] N/A вЂ” no external provider/oracle/VRF integration in scope for this spec\n\n### Testing Requirements\n\nThe agent MUST complete ALL before outputting the completion signal:\n\n#### Code Quality\n- [ ] All existing tests pass\n- [ ] New tests added for new functionality\n- [ ] No lint errors\n\n#### Functional Verification\n- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified\n- [ ] Edge cases handled\n- [ ] Error states handled\n\n#### Visual Regression\n- [ ] `pnpm test:visual` passes (all baselines match)\n- [ ] If this spec changes UI: affected baselines regenerated and committed\n- [ ] Local deterministic E2E passes (`pnpm test:e2e`) for user-facing flows\n- [ ] Devnet real-provider E2E: N/A for this spec\n\n#### Visual Verification (if UI)\n- [ ] Desktop view correct\n- [ ] Mobile view correct\n\n#### Console/Network Check (if web)\n- [ ] No JS console errors\n- [ ] No failed network requests\n\n#### Smoke Test (Human-in-the-Loop)\n\n- [ ] Settle a coinflip match в†’ transaction appears in profile within seconds\n- [ ] Settle a lord round в†’ transaction appears in profile\n- [ ] Place a closecall bet + settle в†’ join and result rows appear\n- [ ] Pagination loads older transactions correctly\n- [ ] Amounts shown in SOL with USD estimate, match on-chain values\n- [ ] Empty profile shows clean empty state, not broken UI\n- [ ] Unauthenticated request returns 401, not data\n\n### Iteration Instructions\n\nIf ANY check fails:\n1. Identify the specific issue\n2. Fix the code\n3. Re-run tests\n4. Re-verify all criteria\n5. Check again\n\n**Only when ALL checks pass, output:** `<promise>DONE</promise>`\n\n### Post-Completion: Gap Analysis\n\nAfter the spec loop outputs `<promise>DONE</promise>`, `spec-loop.sh` automatically runs\n`/gap-analysis {id} --non-interactive` which:\n1. Audits every FR acceptance criterion against the codebase\n2. Writes `docs/specs/008-user-profile/gap-analysis.md` with inventory + audit + recommendations\n3. Annotates FR checkboxes with HTML comment evidence (`<!-- satisfied: ... -->`)\n4. Commits everything together with the completion commit\n","numLines":369,"startLine":1,"totalLines":369}}}
