{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WffBy2rJDSTEwXA4hML3Ae","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect. Now let me create a comprehensive summary report based on all the information I've gathered.\n\n## Summary Report: Authentication in Local E2E Test Environment\n\nBased on my thorough analysis of the codebase, here's how authentication works in the local E2E test environment and whether a test can successfully navigate to `/profile` and see real transaction data:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Auth Flow Overview**\n\nThe authentication system uses a **commit-response JWT challenge-signing model**:\n\n1. **Frontend requests a challenge** (`/auth/challenge`) вЂ” Backend generates a human-readable message containing wallet address, cluster, nonce, and timestamps\n2. **Frontend signs the message** with the wallet's private key using Ed25519\n3. **Frontend verifies the signature** (`/auth/verify`) вЂ” Backend validates the signature and issues JWT tokens\n4. **Access token is stored in memory** in `auth-store.ts` (NOT localStorage, only refresh token persists)\n5. **Subsequent requests include JWT Bearer token** in Authorization header\n\n---\n\n### **2. Access Token Management** (`auth-store.ts`)\n\n- **In-memory storage**: `getAccessToken()` returns null if token is expired (checks with 30s buffer before expiry)\n- **Persistence**: Only the refresh token is persisted in localStorage (`rng-utopia:session`)\n- **Auto-refresh**: SessionContext schedules proactive refresh ~5 minutes before access token expiry\n- **Auto-login on wallet connect**: When wallet connects, SessionContext automatically:\n  - Checks for existing persisted session matching the wallet\n  - If access token is still valid, reuses it (silent restore)\n  - If access token expired, attempts silent refresh with refresh token\n  - If refresh fails, triggers new authentication (challenge-response flow)\n\n---\n\n### **3. JWT Signing Configuration**\n\n**Backend (`config.ts`)**:\n```typescript\njwtSecret: (() => {\n  const explicit = process.env.JWT_SECRET;\n  if (explicit) return new TextEncoder().encode(explicit);\n  // Derive from first 32 bytes of server keypair secret key\n  const kp = parseKeypair(requireEnv(\"SERVER_KEYPAIR\"));\n  return kp.secretKey.slice(0, 32);\n})()\n```\n\n**Local E2E setup (`run-e2e-local.sh`)**:\n- Generates a **deterministic backend keypair** (stored in `.local-backend-keypair.json`)\n- Passes `SERVER_KEYPAIR` as a JSON array of secret key bytes to the backend\n- Backend derives JWT secret from the first 32 bytes of this keypair\n- **Key point**: The JWT secret is **deterministic** in local E2E tests because the backend keypair is generated once and reused\n\n---\n\n### **4. TestWalletProvider Integration**\n\n**Wallet injection flow** (`fixtures.ts` в†’ `TestWalletWrapper.tsx` в†’ `TestWalletProvider.tsx`):\n\n1. **Playwright fixture** (`fixtures.ts` line 53-56): Injects keypair seed via `addInitScript`:\n   ```javascript\n   await context.addInitScript((seed: number[]) => {\n     window.__TEST_WALLET_SEED__ = new Uint8Array(seed);\n   }, seedArray);\n   ```\n\n2. **TestWalletWrapper** reads the seed from `window.__TEST_WALLET_SEED__`\n\n3. **TestWalletProvider** provides `signMessage()` using `nacl.sign.detached()` вЂ” **identical to real wallet signature**\n\n4. **WalletProvider.tsx** (line 96-102): Detects `VITE_TEST_WALLET=true` and lazy-loads `TestWalletWrapper`\n\n---\n\n### **5. SessionContext Auto-Authentication**\n\n**In `SessionContext.tsx` (lines 172-219)**:\n\nWhen wallet connects:\n1. Checks for persisted session matching the wallet address\n2. If found and access token still valid в†’ **silent restore** (no network call)\n3. If access token expired в†’ **silent refresh** with refresh token\n4. If refresh fails в†’ **automatic `authenticate()` call** with challenge-response signing\n\n**Critical**: This all happens automatically on wallet connect. **No manual trigger needed.**\n\n---\n\n### **6. Profile Endpoint Authentication**\n\n**Backend** (`index.ts` lines 84-89):\n```typescript\napp.use(\n  \"/profile/*\",\n  createJwtAuthMiddleware({ jwtSecret: config.jwtSecret, requireAllMethods: true }),\n);\n```\n\n- Profile routes require JWT Bearer token on **ALL HTTP methods** (not just POST)\n- The middleware (`jwt-auth.ts`) extracts the token from `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header\n- Sets `c.set(\"wallet\", payload.sub)` for downstream handlers\n- Returns 401 if token missing or invalid\n\n**Frontend** (`useTransactions.ts` lines 49-56):\n- Fetches `/profile/transactions?limit=20`\n- Includes `Authorization: Bearer ${token}` header using `getAccessToken()`\n- Returns empty array (no error, no fetch) if `getAccessToken()` returns null\n\n---\n\n### **7. Can Local E2E Navigate to /profile and See Transaction Data?**\n\n**YES, with caveats**:\n\n**What works:**\n- вњ… Wallet auto-connects (TestWalletProvider auto-connects on mount)\n- вњ… JWT challenge-response signing works (nacl.sign.detached produces valid Ed25519 signatures)\n- вњ… Backend JWT secret is deterministic (derived from the same server keypair every run)\n- вњ… SessionContext auto-authenticates on wallet connect\n- вњ… Profile endpoint accepts Bearer token\n- вњ… Transaction data can be fetched if `/profile/transactions` endpoint is implemented and DB has test data\n\n**What doesn't work automatically:**\n- вќЊ Transaction data won't exist unless explicitly inserted into the test DB\n  - Backend runs migrations (line 116 in `run-e2e-local.sh`)\n  - But no seed data or test fixtures insert match records\n  - You need to create matches via the `/fairness/matches/create` endpoint (which also requires JWT)\n  \n- вќЊ No E2E test currently navigates to `/profile`\n  - Smoke test (00-smoke.spec.ts) only checks app load and wallet button\n  - Lifecycle tests focus on game creation/joining, not profile view\n  - You'd need to write a new test\n\n---\n\n### **8. Key Files**\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/lib/auth-store.ts` | In-memory access token + localStorage refresh token storage |\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/context/SessionContext.tsx` | JWT auto-auth on wallet connect, token refresh scheduling |\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/lib/auth-api.ts` | Thin fetch wrappers for `/auth/*` endpoints |\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/wallet/src/test/TestWalletProvider.tsx` | Deterministic keypair signing for E2E |\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/fixtures.ts` | Playwright dual-player fixture with seed injection |\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/auth.ts` | Challenge generation, signature verification, JWT issuance |\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/profile.ts` | `/profile/transactions` endpoint (requires JWT) |\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/scripts/run-e2e-local.sh` | Local E2E orchestration (validator + backend + tests) |\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/config.ts` | JWT secret derivation (deterministic in local E2E) |"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aef701b3fb31f74a9 (use SendMessage with to: 'aef701b3fb31f74a9' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 68965\ntool_uses: 38\nduration_ms: 137686</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b99e2185-20b1-487e-a0a4-b3fb9a756d45","uuid":"3847687e-857f-4c76-b535-e91121eb917e","timestamp":"2026-03-19T19:16:28.218Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand how authentication works in the local E2E test environment. Specifically:\n\n1. Read `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/lib/auth-store.ts` вЂ” how does getAccessToken() work?\n2. Check how the frontend handles auth when wallet is connected вЂ” is there auto-login?\n3. Look at the TestWalletProvider or similar test wallet integration\n4. Check if the local E2E backend (run-e2e-local.sh) sets up JWT signing keys\n5. Read `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/fixtures.ts` to see if auth is set up\n\nThe goal is to determine if a local E2E test can navigate to /profile and see real transaction data (i.e., whether JWT auth works in local E2E tests).\n\nBe thorough вЂ” read each file completely.","agentId":"aef701b3fb31f74a9","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect. Now let me create a comprehensive summary report based on all the information I've gathered.\n\n## Summary Report: Authentication in Local E2E Test Environment\n\nBased on my thorough analysis of the codebase, here's how authentication works in the local E2E test environment and whether a test can successfully navigate to `/profile` and see real transaction data:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Auth Flow Overview**\n\nThe authentication system uses a **commit-response JWT challenge-signing model**:\n\n1. **Frontend requests a challenge** (`/auth/challenge`) вЂ” Backend generates a human-readable message containing wallet address, cluster, nonce, and timestamps\n2. **Frontend signs the message** with the wallet's private key using Ed25519\n3. **Frontend verifies the signature** (`/auth/verify`) вЂ” Backend validates the signature and issues JWT tokens\n4. **Access token is stored in memory** in `auth-store.ts` (NOT localStorage, only refresh token persists)\n5. **Subsequent requests include JWT Bearer token** in Authorization header\n\n---\n\n### **2. Access Token Management** (`auth-store.ts`)\n\n- **In-memory storage**: `getAccessToken()` returns null if token is expired (checks with 30s buffer before expiry)\n- **Persistence**: Only the refresh token is persisted in localStorage (`rng-utopia:session`)\n- **Auto-refresh**: SessionContext schedules proactive refresh ~5 minutes before access token expiry\n- **Auto-login on wallet connect**: When wallet connects, SessionContext automatically:\n  - Checks for existing persisted session matching the wallet\n  - If access token is still valid, reuses it (silent restore)\n  - If access token expired, attempts silent refresh with refresh token\n  - If refresh fails, triggers new authentication (challenge-response flow)\n\n---\n\n### **3. JWT Signing Configuration**\n\n**Backend (`config.ts`)**:\n```typescript\njwtSecret: (() => {\n  const explicit = process.env.JWT_SECRET;\n  if (explicit) return new TextEncoder().encode(explicit);\n  // Derive from first 32 bytes of server keypair secret key\n  const kp = parseKeypair(requireEnv(\"SERVER_KEYPAIR\"));\n  return kp.secretKey.slice(0, 32);\n})()\n```\n\n**Local E2E setup (`run-e2e-local.sh`)**:\n- Generates a **deterministic backend keypair** (stored in `.local-backend-keypair.json`)\n- Passes `SERVER_KEYPAIR` as a JSON array of secret key bytes to the backend\n- Backend derives JWT secret from the first 32 bytes of this keypair\n- **Key point**: The JWT secret is **deterministic** in local E2E tests because the backend keypair is generated once and reused\n\n---\n\n### **4. TestWalletProvider Integration**\n\n**Wallet injection flow** (`fixtures.ts` в†’ `TestWalletWrapper.tsx` в†’ `TestWalletProvider.tsx`):\n\n1. **Playwright fixture** (`fixtures.ts` line 53-56): Injects keypair seed via `addInitScript`:\n   ```javascript\n   await context.addInitScript((seed: number[]) => {\n     window.__TEST_WALLET_SEED__ = new Uint8Array(seed);\n   }, seedArray);\n   ```\n\n2. **TestWalletWrapper** reads the seed from `window.__TEST_WALLET_SEED__`\n\n3. **TestWalletProvider** provides `signMessage()` using `nacl.sign.detached()` вЂ” **identical to real wallet signature**\n\n4. **WalletProvider.tsx** (line 96-102): Detects `VITE_TEST_WALLET=true` and lazy-loads `TestWalletWrapper`\n\n---\n\n### **5. SessionContext Auto-Authentication**\n\n**In `SessionContext.tsx` (lines 172-219)**:\n\nWhen wallet connects:\n1. Checks for persisted session matching the