{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DFVxg9prcN7hYUyStDkuJT","type":"tool_result","content":"     1в†’/**\n     2в†’ * Local lifecycle E2E test: create в†’ join в†’ resolve в†’ claim.\n     3в†’ *\n     4в†’ * Uses two isolated browser contexts (Player A and Player B) with\n     5в†’ * deterministic keypairs. The local validator has mock-VRF enabled,\n     6в†’ * and the randomness account is pre-loaded with fulfilled data\n     7в†’ * (byte[0] = 2 в†’ HEADS в†’ creator wins when they chose HEADS).\n     8в†’ *\n     9в†’ * Prerequisites (handled by localnet-bootstrap.sh):\n    10в†’ * - solana-test-validator running with coinflip + platform programs\n    11в†’ * - Orao mock accounts pre-loaded (network state, treasury, randomness)\n    12в†’ */\n    13в†’import { test, expect } from \"./fixtures\";\n    14в†’import * as po from \"./helpers/page-objects\";\n    15в†’import { fundTestWallets, PLAYER_A } from \"./helpers/wallets\";\n    16в†’import { initializeLocalnet } from \"./helpers/localnet-setup\";\n    17в†’import {\n    18в†’  assertMatchCreated,\n    19в†’  assertMatchClosed,\n    20в†’  assertTreasuryFee,\n    21в†’  snapshotBalance,\n    22в†’  getTreasuryAddress,\n    23в†’} from \"./helpers/on-chain\";\n    24в†’\n    25в†’// в”Ђв”Ђ Suite setup в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\n    26в†’\n    27в†’test.beforeAll(async () => {\n    28в†’  // Fund test wallets and initialize program configs\n    29в†’  await fundTestWallets();\n    30в†’  await initializeLocalnet();\n    31в†’});\n    32в†’\n    33в†’// в”Ђв”Ђ Full lifecycle test в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\n    34в†’\n    35в†’test(\"coinflip full lifecycle: create в†’ join в†’ resolve в†’ claim\", async ({\n    36в†’  playerAPage,\n    37в†’  playerBPage,\n    38в†’  connection,\n    39в†’}) => {\n    40в†’  const SIDE_HEADS = 0;\n    41в†’  const ENTRY_AMOUNT = 5_000_000; // 0.005 SOL in lamports\n    42в†’\n    43в†’  // Track console errors in both contexts\n    44в†’  const consoleA = po.trackConsoleErrors(playerAPage);\n    45в†’  const consoleB = po.trackConsoleErrors(playerBPage);\n    46в†’\n    47в†’  // 1. Player A navigates and creates a match (iron tier, heads)\n    48в†’  await po.navigateToCoinflip(playerAPage);\n    49в†’  await po.createMatch(playerAPage, \"iron\", \"heads\");\n    50в†’\n    51в†’  // Player A should see the active match in \"waiting\" state\n    52в†’  await expect(\n    53в†’    playerAPage.locator(po.sel.activeMatchWaiting),\n    54в†’  ).toBeVisible({ timeout: 10_000 });\n    55в†’\n    56в†’  // в”Ђв”Ђ On-chain: verify match PDA after creation в”Ђв”Ђ\n    57в†’  const { matchPda } = await assertMatchCreated(\n    58в†’    connection,\n    59в†’    PLAYER_A.publicKey,\n    60в†’    SIDE_HEADS,\n    61в†’  );\n    62в†’\n    63в†’  // 2. Player B navigates (after match is created) and sees it in the lobby\n    64в†’  await po.navigateToCoinflip(playerBPage);\n    65в†’  await po.waitForLobbyMatch(playerBPage, 15_000);\n    66в†’\n    67в†’  // 3. Player B joins the match\n    68в†’  await po.joinMatch(playerBPage);\n    69в†’\n    70в†’  // в”Ђв”Ђ On-chain: snapshot treasury before resolution/claim в”Ђв”Ђ\n    71в†’  const treasury = await getTreasuryAddress(connection);\n    72в†’  const treasuryBefore = await snapshotBalance(connection, treasury);\n    73в†’\n    74в†’  // 4. Both players wait for the backend-settled result.\n    75в†’  const [resultA, resultB] = await Promise.all([\n    76в†’    po.waitForResult(playerAPage, 30_000),\n    77в†’    po.waitForResult(playerBPage, 30_000),\n    78в†’  ]);\n    79в†’\n    80в†’  // 5. Verify results are complementary.\n    81в†’  expect(resultA).not.toBe(resultB);\n    82в†’\n    83в†’  // 6. Settlement is backend-driven, so the match PDA should already be closed.\n    84в†’  await assertMatchClosed(connection, matchPda);\n    85в†’\n    86в†’  // в”Ђв”Ђ On-chain: verify treasury received the 3% fee в”Ђв”Ђ\n    87в†’  await assertTreasuryFee(connection, treasury, treasuryBefore, ENTRY_AMOUNT);\n    88в†’\n    89в†’  // 7. Winner can return to the lobby after settlement.\n    90в†’  const winnerPage = resultA === \"won\" ? playerAPage : playerBPage;\n    91в†’  await expect(\n    92в†’    winnerPage.locator(po.sel.sidebar).locator(\"button\", { hasText: \"Back to Lobby\" }),\n    93в†’  ).toBeVisible();\n    94в†’  await po.backToLobby(winnerPage);\n    95в†’  await po.assertLobbyEmpty(winnerPage);\n    96в†’\n    97в†’  // No unhandled console errors in either context\n    98в†’  consoleA.assertClean();\n    99в†’  consoleB.assertClean();\n   100в†’});\n   101в†’"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b99e2185-20b1-487e-a0a4-b3fb9a756d45","uuid":"c226c8a2-50bb-4786-b79b-45f869dd9073","timestamp":"2026-03-19T19:17:15.541Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/03-lifecycle.spec.ts","content":"/**\n * Local lifecycle E2E test: create в†’ join в†’ resolve в†’ claim.\n *\n * Uses two isolated browser contexts (Player A and Player B) with\n * deterministic keypairs. The local validator has mock-VRF enabled,\n * and the randomness account is pre-loaded with fulfilled data\n * (byte[0] = 2 в†’ HEADS в†’ creator wins when they chose HEADS).\n *\n * Prerequisites (handled by localnet-bootstrap.sh):\n * - solana-test-validator running with coinflip + platform programs\n * - Orao mock accounts pre-loaded (network state, treasury, randomness)\n */\nimport { test, expect } from \"./fixtures\";\nimport * as po from \"./helpers/page-objects\";\nimport { fundTestWallets, PLAYER_A } from \"./helpers/wallets\";\nimport { initializeLocalnet } from \"./helpers/localnet-setup\";\nimport {\n  assertMatchCreated,\n  assertMatchClosed,\n  assertTreasuryFee,\n  snapshotBalance,\n  getTreasuryAddress,\n} from \"./helpers/on-chain\";\n\n// в”Ђв”Ђ Suite setup в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\n\ntest.beforeAll(async () => {\n  // Fund test wallets and initialize program configs\n  await fundTestWallets();\n  await initializeLocalnet();\n});\n\n// в”Ђв”Ђ Full lifecycle test в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\n\ntest(\"coinflip full lifecycle: create в†’ join в†’ resolve в†’ claim\", async ({\n  playerAPage,\n  playerBPage,\n  connection,\n}) => {\n  const SIDE_HEADS = 0;\n  const ENTRY_AMOUNT = 5_000_000; // 0.005 SOL in lamports\n\n  // Track console errors in both contexts\n  const consoleA = po.trackConsoleErrors(playerAPage);\n  const consoleB = po.trackConsoleErrors(playerBPage);\n\n  // 1. Player A navigates and creates a match (iron tier, heads)\n  await po.navigateToCoinflip(playerAPage);\n  await po.createMatch(playerAPage, \"iron\", \"heads\");\n\n  // Player A should see the active match in \"waiting\" state\n  await expect(\n    playerAPage.locator(po.sel.activeMatchWaiting),\n  ).toBeVisible({ timeout: 10_000 });\n\n  // в”Ђв”Ђ On-chain: verify match PDA after creation в”Ђв”Ђ\n  const { matchPda } = await assertMatchCreated(\n    connection,\n    PLAYER_A.publicKey,\n    SIDE_HEADS,\n  );\n\n  // 2. Player B navigates (after match is created) and sees it in the lobby\n  await po.navigateToCoinflip(playerBPage);\n  await po.waitForLobbyMatch(playerBPage, 15_000);\n\n  // 3. Player B joins the match\n  await po.joinMatch(playerBPage);\n\n  // в”Ђв”Ђ On-chain: snapshot treasury before resolution/claim в”Ђв”Ђ\n  const treasury = await getTreasuryAddress(connection);\n  const treasuryBefore = await snapshotBalance(connection, treasury);\n\n  // 4. Both players wait for the backend-settled result.\n  const [resultA, resultB] = await Promise.all([\n    po.waitForResult(playerAPage, 30_000),\n    po.waitForResult(playerBPage, 30_000),\n  ]);\n\n  // 5. Verify results are complementary.\n  expect(resultA).not.toBe(resultB);\n\n  // 6. Settlement is backend-driven, so the match PDA should already be closed.\n  await assertMatchClosed(connection, matchPda);\n\n  // в”Ђв”Ђ On-chain: verify treasury received the 3% fee в”Ђв”Ђ\n  await assertTreasuryFee(connection, treasury, treasuryBefore, ENTRY_AMOUNT);\n\n  // 7. Winner can return to the lobby after settlement.\n  const winnerPage = resultA === \"won\" ? playerAPage : playerBPage;\n  await expect(\n    winnerPage.locator(po.sel.sidebar).locator(\"button\", { hasText: \"Back to Lobby\" }),\n  ).toBeVisible();\n  await po.backToLobby(winnerPage);\n  await po.assertLobbyEmpty(winnerPage);\n\n  // No unhandled console errors in either context\n  consoleA.assertClean();\n  consoleB.assertClean();\n});\n","numLines":101,"startLine":1,"totalLines":101}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_011t38iAvZXZHcgV37B5CihT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a complete picture. Let me think about the approach for the local E2E profile test.\n\nThe key consideration: The local E2E tests require the full infrastructure (validator, backend, programs deployed). In these tests:\n\n1. Wallet auto-connects via TestWalletProvider\n2. SessionContext auto-authenticates via JWT challenge-response\n3. After a coinflip match is created and settled, the backend writes user_transaction rows\n4. Navigating to /profile and clicking \"Transactions\" tab should show these rows\n\nHowever, the `ProfileTransactions` component calls `useTransactions()` which fetches from `GET /profile/transactions` with JWT auth. \n\nThe JWT auth depends on `getAccessToken()` from the auth store, which requires the SessionContext to have completed the challenge-response auth flow. In the local E2E tests, the wallet connects automatically and SessionContext should auto-authenticate, though there could be timing issues if the backend isn't ready or the wallet connection hasn't fully established.\n\nI'll create a test that runs through a complete coinflip lifecycle using existing helpers, then navigates to the profile page and verifies the transactions tab displays the expected rows.\n\nWriting the test file... Writing test assertions...\n\nNow I'm thinking about the ProfilePage component and what it needs from the usePlayerProfile hook to render properly.\n\nThe ProfilePage pulls profile data from the mock store via PlayerProfileContext, so it should display the profile header even in local E2E mode. However, the transactions tab fetches from the real backend API through useTransactions, which means the header comes from mock data while the transaction list comes from actual API responses. That should work fine as long as both sources are available.\n\nThere's one potential issue with the SOL/USD price endpointвЂ”the useSolPrice hook calls GET /price/sol-usd, which the local backend should serve by fetching from Pyth Hermes. If the test environment can't reach Hermes, the price will be null and amounts will display as SOL only without the USD conversion.\n\nI'm now thinking through some timing concerns: the wallet should already be connected from the coinflip page, so SessionContext should have completed auth by the time we navigate to /profile. But there's a risk that the profile page loads before auth finishes, which could cause useTransactions to return empty since it only fetches when getAccessToken() returns a valid token. I might need to add waits or retries to handle this. I'm also considering the row countвЂ”Player A creates a match as the creator. I need to verify that the `VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL` environment variable is properly configured for local E2E testing, so let me check the Playwright config to see what's set up.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6993,"cache_read_input_tokens":59589,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":6993},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b99e2185-20b1-487e-a0a4-b3fb9a756d45","uuid":"58cc8ae6-9bae-4d68-b356-f211c10a2b6b"}
