{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NZFhXuiJQHRhGGjYYwR6Jp","type":"tool_result","content":"     1в†’/**\n     2в†’ * useTransactions вЂ” fetches transaction history from the real API.\n     3в†’ *\n     4в†’ * Uses JWT auth (from auth-store) and cursor-based pagination.\n     5в†’ */\n     6в†’\n     7в†’import { useState, useCallback, useEffect, useRef } from \"react\";\n     8в†’import { getAccessToken } from \"../../../lib/auth-store\";\n     9в†’import type { GameId, TransactionEvent } from \"../types\";\n    10в†’\n    11в†’const BACKEND_URL = (\n    12в†’  (import.meta as unknown as { env: Record<string, string | undefined> }).env\n    13в†’    .VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL ?? \"http://127.0.0.1:3100\"\n    14в†’).replace(/\\/$/, \"\");\n    15в†’\n    16в†’interface ApiTransaction {\n    17в†’  id: string;\n    18в†’  game: string;\n    19в†’  matchId: string;\n    20в†’  event: TransactionEvent;\n    21в†’  amountLamports: string;\n    22в†’  txSig: string | null;\n    23в†’  createdAt: string;\n    24в†’}\n    25в†’\n    26в†’interface ApiResponse {\n    27в†’  transactions: ApiTransaction[];\n    28в†’  nextCursor: string | null;\n    29в†’}\n    30в†’\n    31в†’export interface Transaction {\n    32в†’  id: string;\n    33в†’  gameId: GameId;\n    34в†’  matchId: string;\n    35в†’  event: TransactionEvent;\n    36в†’  amountLamports: string;\n    37в†’  txSig: string | null;\n    38в†’  createdAt: string;\n    39в†’}\n    40в†’\n    41в†’export function useTransactions(game?: string) {\n    42в†’  const [transactions, setTransactions] = useState<Transaction[]>([]);\n    43в†’  const [nextCursor, setNextCursor] = useState<string | null>(null);\n    44в†’  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);\n    45в†’  const [loadingMore, setLoadingMore] = useState(false);\n    46в†’  const [error, setError] = useState<string | null>(null);\n    47в†’  const abortRef = useRef<AbortController | null>(null);\n    48в†’\n    49в†’  const fetchPage = useCallback(\n    50в†’    async (cursor?: string) => {\n    51в†’      const token = getAccessToken();\n    52в†’      if (!token) {\n    53в†’        setTransactions([]);\n    54в†’        setLoading(false);\n    55в†’        return;\n    56в†’      }\n    57в†’\n    58в†’      // Build query string\n    59в†’      const parts = [\"limit=20\"];\n    60в†’      if (cursor) parts.push(`cursor=${encodeURIComponent(cursor)}`);\n    61в†’      if (game) parts.push(`game=${encodeURIComponent(game)}`);\n    62в†’      const qs = parts.join(\"&\");\n    63в†’\n    64в†’      // Abort any in-flight request\n    65в†’      abortRef.current?.abort();\n    66в†’      const controller = new AbortController();\n    67в†’      abortRef.current = controller;\n    68в†’\n    69в†’      try {\n    70в†’        const res = await fetch(\n    71в†’          `${BACKEND_URL}/profile/transactions?${qs}`,\n    72в†’          {\n    73в†’            headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` },\n    74в†’            signal: controller.signal,\n    75в†’          },\n    76в†’        );\n    77в†’        if (!res.ok) throw new Error(`HTTP ${res.status}`);\n    78в†’        const data: ApiResponse = await res.json();\n    79в†’\n    80в†’        const mapped: Transaction[] = data.transactions.map((tx) => ({\n    81в†’          id: tx.id,\n    82в†’          gameId: tx.game as GameId,\n    83в†’          matchId: tx.matchId,\n    84в†’          event: tx.event,\n    85в†’          amountLamports: tx.amountLamports,\n    86в†’          txSig: tx.txSig,\n    87в†’          createdAt: tx.createdAt,\n    88в†’        }));\n    89в†’\n    90в†’        if (cursor) {\n    91в†’          setTransactions((prev) => [...prev, ...mapped]);\n    92в†’        } else {\n    93в†’          setTransactions(mapped);\n    94в†’        }\n    95в†’        setNextCursor(data.nextCursor);\n    96в†’        setError(null);\n    97в†’      } catch (err) {\n    98в†’        if (err instanceof Error && err.name === \"AbortError\") return;\n    99в†’        setError(err instanceof Error ? err.message : \"Failed to fetch\");\n   100в†’      } finally {\n   101в†’        setLoading(false);\n   102в†’        setLoadingMore(false);\n   103в†’      }\n   104в†’    },\n   105в†’    [game],\n   106в†’  );\n   107в†’\n   108в†’  useEffect(() => {\n   109в†’    setLoading(true);\n   110в†’    setTransactions([]);\n   111в†’    setNextCursor(null);\n   112в†’    fetchPage();\n   113в†’    return () => abortRef.current?.abort();\n   114в†’  }, [fetchPage]);\n   115в†’\n   116в†’  const loadMore = useCallback(() => {\n   117в†’    if (!nextCursor || loadingMore) return;\n   118в†’    setLoadingMore(true);\n   119в†’    fetchPage(nextCursor);\n   120в†’  }, [nextCursor, loadingMore, fetchPage]);\n   121в†’\n   122в†’  return { transactions, loading, loadingMore, error, nextCursor, loadMore };\n   123в†’}\n   124в†’"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b99e2185-20b1-487e-a0a4-b3fb9a756d45","uuid":"fd937f98-d46a-456b-bb91-3e9ba530111f","timestamp":"2026-03-19T19:17:56.142Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/player-profile/hooks/useTransactions.ts","content":"/**\n * useTransactions вЂ” fetches transaction history from the real API.\n *\n * Uses JWT auth (from auth-store) and cursor-based pagination.\n */\n\nimport { useState, useCallback, useEffect, useRef } from \"react\";\nimport { getAccessToken } from \"../../../lib/auth-store\";\nimport type { GameId, TransactionEvent } from \"../types\";\n\nconst BACKEND_URL = (\n  (import.meta as unknown as { env: Record<string, string | undefined> }).env\n    .VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL ?? \"http://127.0.0.1:3100\"\n).replace(/\\/$/, \"\");\n\ninterface ApiTransaction {\n  id: string;\n  game: string;\n  matchId: string;\n  event: TransactionEvent;\n  amountLamports: string;\n  txSig: string | null;\n  createdAt: string;\n}\n\ninterface ApiResponse {\n  transactions: ApiTransaction[];\n  nextCursor: string | null;\n}\n\nexport interface Transaction {\n  id: string;\n  gameId: GameId;\n  matchId: string;\n  event: TransactionEvent;\n  amountLamports: string;\n  txSig: string | null;\n  createdAt: string;\n}\n\nexport function useTransactions(game?: string) {\n  const [transactions, setTransactions] = useState<Transaction[]>([]);\n  const [nextCursor, setNextCursor] = useState<string | null>(null);\n  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);\n  const [loadingMore, setLoadingMore] = useState(false);\n  const [error, setError] = useState<string | null>(null);\n  const abortRef = useRef<AbortController | null>(null);\n\n  const fetchPage = useCallback(\n    async (cursor?: string) => {\n      const token = getAccessToken();\n      if (!token) {\n        setTransactions([]);\n        setLoading(false);\n        return;\n      }\n\n      // Build query string\n      const parts = [\"limit=20\"];\n      if (cursor) parts.push(`cursor=${encodeURIComponent(cursor)}`);\n      if (game) parts.push(`game=${encodeURIComponent(game)}`);\n      const qs = parts.join(\"&\");\n\n      // Abort any in-flight request\n      abortRef.current?.abort();\n      const controller = new AbortController();\n      abortRef.current = controller;\n\n      try {\n        const res = await fetch(\n          `${BACKEND_URL}/profile/transactions?${qs}`,\n          {\n            headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` },\n            signal: controller.signal,\n          },\n        );\n        if (!res.ok) throw new Error(`HTTP ${res.status}`);\n        const data: ApiResponse = await res.json();\n\n        const mapped: Transaction[] = data.transactions.map((tx) => ({\n          id: tx.id,\n          gameId: tx.game as GameId,\n          matchId: tx.matchId,\n          event: tx.event,\n          amountLamports: tx.amountLamports,\n          txSig: tx.txSig,\n          createdAt: tx.createdAt,\n        }));\n\n        if (cursor) {\n          setTransactions((prev) => [...prev, ...mapped]);\n        } else {\n          setTransactions(mapped);\n        }\n        setNextCursor(data.nextCursor);\n        setError(null);\n      } catch (err) {\n        if (err instanceof Error && err.name === \"AbortError\") return;\n        setError(err instanceof Error ? err.message : \"Failed to fetch\");\n      } finally {\n        setLoading(false);\n        setLoadingMore(false);\n      }\n    },\n    [game],\n  );\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    setLoading(true);\n    setTransactions([]);\n    setNextCursor(null);\n    fetchPage();\n    return () => abortRef.current?.abort();\n  }, [fetchPage]);\n\n  const loadMore = useCallback(() => {\n    if (!nextCursor || loadingMore) return;\n    setLoadingMore(true);\n    fetchPage(nextCursor);\n  }, [nextCursor, loadingMore, fetchPage]);\n\n  return { transactions, loading, loadingMore, error, nextCursor, loadMore };\n}\n","numLines":124,"startLine":1,"totalLines":124}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01BG6Y5qdCHZMeWE5XMrC9Qu","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the issue. The `useTransactions` hook calls `getAccessToken()` from `auth-store`. If the access token is null (not authenticated), it returns empty and sets loading to false. \n\nThe key question: when navigating to /profile after playing a coinflip game, will the user already be authenticated? Let me think:\n\n1. The test wallet auto-connects on page load (TestWalletProvider)\n2. SessionContext detects wallet connection and triggers auth flow\n3. Auth flow: challenge request в†’ sign challenge в†’ verify signature в†’ get JWT\n\nThis should complete quickly (within a second or two). After playing through a complete coinflip lifecycle (which takes ~30s with settlement), auth should definitely be complete.\n \nWhen the page reloads at `/profile`, the test wallet auto-connects again and SessionContext checks for a persisted refresh token in localStorage. Since the token was stored after the coinflip game, it should perform a silent refresh rather than triggering the full auth flow again, so `getAccessToken()` should return a valid token immediately.\n\nHowever, there's a potential race condition: the transactions component might mount and call `useTransactions` before the auth refresh completes, causing `getAccessToken()` to return undefined momentarily.\n\nThe hook only fetches once on mount via `useEffect`, so if auth hasn't finished by then, it won't re-fetch when the token becomes available later. For the E2E test, I could navigate to the coinflip page first to ensure auth completes, then navigate to the profile pageвЂ”but a full page reload would reset the auth state anyway.\n\nActually, when `page.goto()` loads the profile page fresh, the SPA boots up and SessionContext checks for a persisted refresh token in localStorage from the previous auth. The real question is whether `useTransactions` fires its initial fetch before or after SessionContext completes the silent refresh, since that's an async network call.\n\nThe simplest fix is to use client-side navigation instead of a full page reloadвЂ”either by clicking a profile link in the nav if one exists, or by staying in the same browser context after the coinflip settlement and navigating that way to preserve the auth state.\n\nBut there's a deeper issue: if `getAccessToken()` returns null when the transactions component first mounts, it immediately renders an empty state and stops trying to fetch. Even when auth completes later, there's no mechanism to retry the fetch, so the test would see \"No transactions yet\" and fail even though the data exists in the database.\n\nI need to decide between fixing the hook itself to re-fetch on auth state changes, using client-side navigation to preserve auth state in memory, waiting for auth before navigating, or navigating then reloading. Client-side navigation seems cleanest since it keeps the page in memory and preserves the auth token. Let me check if there's a navigation link I can use instead of a full page reload, and I should also consider how the wallet connection worked in the local E2E test.\n\nThe real problem is a race condition: when I reload the page with `page.goto()`, the in-memory auth store gets wiped but localStorage persists. SessionContext tries to restore from the refresh token, but `useTransactions` fires before that restoration completes and gets a null access token. The timing depends on whether SessionContext can synchronously check localStorage before the transactions hook runs.\n\nI'm realizing that waiting for the profile header to appear doesn't guarantee JWT auth is complete, since the mock profile store works independently. Instead, I should wait for the auth restoration to finish before triggering the transactions fetchвЂ”maybe by waiting for a specific condition that indicates the access token is available. should be complete.\n\nLet me verify this by checking the ProfilePage code... yes, the default tab is \"stats\", so the Transactions component only mounts when clicked. This means I can navigate to /profile, wait for the profile header to load (indicating auth has completed), then click the Transactions tab to trigger the hook with a valid token available.\n\nBut there's a potential race condition if auth hasn't finished by the time I click the tab. I should add a safety measureвЂ”either wait for specific network responses like the auth verify request, or just wait for the profile header to appear and add a small delay to ensure auth completes before clicking Transactions.\n\nSetting up the test file...\n\nI'm setting up the test fixtures and initializing the wallets and localnet, then creating a test that has two players perform a coinflip match and wait for both to receive results.\n\nNow I'm navigating Player A to their profile page, waiting for the auth verification to complete and the profile header to load, then clicking on the Transactions tab.\n\nSetting up assertions for the transaction table...\n\nI'm realizing there's a potential issue with the `waitForResponse` approach вЂ” if the session was already authenticated on the coinflip page and the token persisted, the browser might skip the auth flow entirely through silent restoration. This means the `/auth/verify` endpoint might never get called when loading the profile page. Looking at how SessionContext works, it checks for a persisted session first, and if the access token is still valid, it restores silently without any network requests. Only if the token expired would it make a refresh call, or if there's no session at all would it do the full challenge-response flow.\n\nAfter playing coinflip, the access token was valid, but navigating to a new page clears the in-memory token while the refresh token stays in localStorage. So SessionContext would find the persisted session, realize the access token is gone, and call `/auth/refresh` to get a new one вЂ” not `/auth/verify`.\n\nThis is getting too complicated to synchronize with. I think a simpler approach would be to navigate within the SPA itself by clicking a nav link to the profile page, which avoids a full page reload and keeps the in-memory auth token intact. I just need to figure out what navigation element to click.\n\nActually, I could use client-side navigation like `window.location.href = '/profile'`, but that triggers a full reload anyway. Let me look for a profile nav link I can click instead.\n\nWait, I'm overcomplicating this. The real question is what happens after a full page reload to `/profile` вЂ” the TestWalletProvider reconnects instantly from the seed, the SessionContext checks localStorage for a refresh token, and if it finds one, it automatically re-authenticates. So the auth state should persist across the navigation.\n\nThe timing concern is whether that auth refresh completes before the test tries to interact with the page. Since we're on localhost, the network call should be sub-100ms, which means by the time the page load settles and the test clicks the Transactions tab, the auth should already be done. The test is waiting for the page to load anyway, so there's a natural synchronization point there.\n\nTo be extra safe though, I could set up a response listener for the auth endpoint before navigating, then await that promise to ensure the refresh completes before proceeding.\n\nSetting up auth response listener... I'm setting up a response listener that waits for the auth endpoint to respond successfully before proceeding with navigation, but I'm realizing there's a potential issueвЂ”if auth already completed before the page navigated, the listener would timeout waiting for a call that never happens. Let me trace through what actually happens when the page loads: the app mounts fresh, the wallet provider auto-connects, and then SessionContext's effect triggers with the new address to refresh the session.\n\nWhen checking the existing session, it loads from localStorage and evaluates the token stateвЂ”if the access token is expired (which it would be after a reload since it's only in-memory), it calls refreshAuth to hit the /auth/refresh endpoint. So there should always be a network call to intercept, making the waitForResponse approach viable. But I need to verify whether the access token gets persisted to localStorage or stays in-memory only. for any response matching `/auth/` to handle both refresh and initial auth flows. Since the test wallet is deterministic, the same keypair is used consistently, so the localStorage refresh token should work reliably across the coinflip page and profile navigation.\n\nIf the refresh call fails, the SessionContext will fall back to a full auth challenge, but either way there's an auth endpoint hit that the test can catch. Now I'm thinking through what transaction rows Player A should have in the database: a creator join row written at match creation with the wager amount, and then either a win or loss row at settlement depending on the outcome.\n\nSo Player A ends up with exactly 2 rows total. I'm checking how the API maps game namesвЂ”`coinflip` stays as `coinflip` in the response (only `lord` and `closecall` get remapped), while the frontend translates it to `\"Flip You\"` for display.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4063,"cache_read_input_tokens":66582,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4063},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b99e2185-20b1-487e-a0a4-b3fb9a756d45","uuid":"2db29f50-5aa0-4356-acb9-c50ee9a6b2cd"}
