{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01XUKXbuY87eYKiwxAzde8Qk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the flow. After `page.goto(\"/profile\")`:\n\n1. App mounts fresh\n2. TestWalletProvider auto-connects в†’ `connected = true`, `publicKey` set\n3. SessionContext useEffect triggers (line 173)\n4. Checks for persisted session matching publicKey\n5. If found with valid refresh token в†’ tries refresh\n6. If refresh succeeds в†’ access token available\n7. If no session or refresh fails в†’ triggers full authenticate (challenge-response)\n\nEither way, there WILL be a network call to `/auth/refresh` or `/auth/challenge`+`/auth/verify`. This confirms that `waitForResponse` for `/auth/` will work.\n\n\nThe `useTransactions` hook depends on `fetchPage` and only runs once at mount, so if the token isn't ready yet, it returns empty and won't retry. I need to make sure `ProfileTransactions` mounts after auth completesвЂ”since the default tab is \"stats\", the component won't load until I click the \"Transactions\" tab, which gives the token time to be available when `fetchPage` executes.\n\nNow I'm thinking through the test flow: navigate to profile, wait for the auth request to finish, click the Transactions tab, wait for the table to load, then verify the rows appear. Before I write the test though, I should check the `run-e2e-local.sh` script to understand how postgres and migrations are set up, since that affects whether the user_transactions table exists.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":623,"cache_read_input_tokens":79512,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":623},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b99e2185-20b1-487e-a0a4-b3fb9a756d45","uuid":"c0d33c9b-e474-4fc0